# Files kept in the repository but excluded from the published plugin
# archive. Claude installs this plugin from the GitHub source tarball
# (the cache under ~/.claude/plugins/cache is an archive extract, not a
# clone) and the Codex installer downloads the same codeload tarball;
# GitHub honors `export-ignore` when generating those archives, so these
# paths never reach a consumer. Runtime-needed files (skills/, shared/,
# scripts/, spec.md, README.md, INSTALL.md, plugin-version.json, and the
# generated .claude*/.codex-plugin payloads) are intentionally not listed.
# See issue ss-15i.

